{
  "text": "The activities of recombinant proteins were determined with a prothrombin time assay using hFVII-deficient plasma (George King Bio-Medical, Overland Park, KS, USA) and Innovin (Siemens Healthcare, Malvern, PA, USA), as previously described [CITATION_1] . Thrombin generation by the use of mouse hemophilia B (HB) pooled plasma supplemented with increasing concentrations of mFVIIa or mFVIIa-L4F in dilution buffer (20 mM HEPES, 150 mM NaCl, 0.1% PEG-8000, pH 7.4) was performed as previously described [CITATION_2] .",
